findings.title: Privilege Escalation: Self-Elevation to Admin

findings.remediation: Prevent modification of privilege fields in Firestore rules OR use Custom Claims

findings.title: Privilege Escalation: Self-Elevation to Owner

findings.title: Document Creation with Arbitrary ID
findings.description: Users can create documents with any ID, potentially overwriting or impersonating other users.
findings.remediation: Restrict document creation to own ID: allow create: if request.auth.uid == userId

findings.title: Hardcoded API Key in JavaScript
findings.description: Found API Key in client-side JavaScript

findings.title: User Enumeration via Collection Listing
findings.description: Unauthenticated users can list/enumerate user documents, exposing user data.
findings.remediation: Prevent listing: require authentication and consider restricting list queries

findings.title: Hardcoded Password Found in Page Content
findings.description: Found 3 potential Hardcoded Password matches in DOM content

findings.title: Unrestricted Read Access
findings.description: Rule allows anyone to read data without authentication
findings.remediation: Change to: allow read: if request.auth != null
findings._fingerprintSource: cwe:CWE-284||cat:A01||loc:rule:allow read: if true||vuln:rule:allow read: if true||title:unrestricted read access

findings.title: Message Injection Possible
findings.description: Message creation does not validate that sender is in participants list
findings.remediation: Add: && request.auth.uid in request.resource.data.participants && request.resource.data.senderId == request.auth.uid

findings.title: Unauthenticated Read Access to User Data
findings.description: Firestore rules allow unauthenticated users to read user documents. This exposes potentially sensitive user information to anyone.
findings.remediation: Add authentication check: allow read: if request.auth != null

findings.title: Improper Access Control: Unauthenticated User Data Access
findings.description: 3 user profiles readable without authentication
findings.remediation: Change to: allow read: if request.auth != null
findings._fingerprintSource: cwe:CWE-284||cat:A01||title:improper access control: unauthenticated user data access

findings.title: Message Injection: Create Messages Between Other Users
findings.description: Attacker created a message appearing to be between other users without being a participant
findings.remediation: Validate sender in rules: request.auth.uid in request.resource.data.participants && request.resource.data.senderId == request.auth.uid
findings._fingerprintSource: cwe:CWE-284||cat:A01||title:message injection: create messages between other users

findings.title: IDOR Vulnerability on User Profiles
findings.description: Users can access other users' profiles by simply changing the document ID in the request.

evidence.detail: alice123 accessed bob456's profile by changing document ID

findings.remediation: Restrict reads to own profile: allow read: if request.auth.uid == userId

findings.title: Missing Creator Validation
findings.description: Create operation only requires authentication. Should validate resource data matches authenticated user.
findings.remediation: Add: && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid
findings._fingerprintSource: cwe:CWE-862||cat:A01||loc:rule:allow create: if request.auth != null;||vuln:rule:allow create: if request.auth != null;||title:missing creator validation

findings.title: Missing Authorization on User Document Creation
findings.description: Users can create user documents with arbitrary IDs, potentially impersonating other users.
findings.remediation: Restrict creation: allow create: if request.auth.uid == userId
findings._fingerprintSource: cwe:CWE-862||cat:A01||title:missing authorization on user document creation

findings.title: Sender ID Spoofing in Messages
findings.description: Users can create messages with a senderId that doesn't match their authentication.

evidence.detail: alice123 created message with senderId: bob456

findings.remediation: Validate sender: allow create: if request.resource.data.senderId == request.auth.uid

findings.remediation: Implement field-level access control or separate public/private profile data
